I really liked this game despite its intermittant sluggishness (some objects hard to click, some new scenes opened slowly, especially in the early parts of the game.) It was nice and long (for me) and took a couple of days to play. I also liked the bonus game which continued the story logically. I got a couple of "this video cannot be played" messages during the bonus play but nothing actually stalled and the scenes played just fine. The artwork was really nice throughout although a few objects were buried in dark spots. I enjoyed the story which was pretty straightforward, not obtuse or full of endless "walking" like some games. The clues and places to play the objects were usually nearby, within a location or two from where it was found. Overall, this game is well thought out and quite entertaining for a casual player.
